> Complete step-by-step explanation of what this project is, what has been done, what each file does, and what comes next.

---

## 1. What Is This Project?

**Goal**: Build a machine-learning system that automatically classifies SMS text messages as either **"ham"** (legitimate) or **"spam"** (junk/scam).

**Why?** A content-trust team needs to:
- Auto-block obvious spam messages
- Flag borderline messages for human review
- Reduce manual review effort

**Dataset**: The **UCI SMS Spam Collection** — 5,574 English SMS messages (~87% ham, ~13% spam), collected between 2009–2012 by Tiago A. Almeida & José María Gómez Hidalgo.

**This is a binary text classification problem** — given a text message, predict one of two classes.

